# Nothing Assistant — Wear OS AI Assistant

A production-quality, standalone Wear OS app for Samsung Galaxy Watch 7 (44mm) that provides a Gemini-powered AI assistant with voice and text input, chat history, and a quick-access Tile.

## Tech Stack & Versions

| Component | Version |
|---|---|
| **Compile SDK / Target SDK** | 36 (Android 16 "Baklava") |
| **Min SDK** | 33 (Wear OS 4+) |
| **Kotlin** | 2.1.0 |
| **AGP (Android Gradle Plugin)** | 9.2.1 |
| **Wear Compose Material3** | 1.5.0 |
| **Wear Compose Foundation** | 1.5.0 |
| **Wear Compose Navigation** | 1.5.0 |
| **Room** | 2.8.4 |
| **OkHttp** | 4.12.0 |
| **Security-Crypto** | 1.1.0 |
| **Wear Tiles** | 1.6.1 |
| **Wear ProtoLayout** | 1.4.1 |

Full dependency list: see `app/build.gradle.kts`.

## How to Build & Run

### Prerequisites
- **Android Studio Ladybug** (2026.x) or newer
- Wear OS emulator with **API 36**, **480×480 round** skin
- A **Gemini API key** from [Google AI Studio](https://ai.google.dev)

### Setup

1. Open the project in Android Studio.
2. Let Gradle sync (this will download all dependencies automatically).
3. If prompted, install the Android SDK for API 36.
4. **Do not build yet** — you need an API key first.

### Getting a Gemini API Key

1. Go to https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
2. Sign in with your Google account.
3. Click **Create API Key** (or use an existing key).
4. Copy the key string (starts with `AIza...`).

### Installing & Testing

1. Connect a Wear OS emulator (480×480 round) or physical Galaxy Watch 7.
2. Build and install the app via Android Studio (Run ▶).
3. **On first launch**, you'll see the onboarding screen:
   - Tap the "Tap to enter API key" field → Wear's keyboard opens.
   - Paste your Gemini API key.
   - Tap "Save & Continue" — the app validates the key before saving.
4. Once validated, you enter the **chat screen**. Tap the mic or "Tap to type" to start a conversation.
5. **To test the Tile:** Add the "Nothing Assistant" tile to your watch face via the phone's Wear OS app or long-press the watch face → customize → tiles.

## Project Structure

```
app/src/main/java/com/nothing/assistant/
├── MainActivity.kt           # Single activity, ambient lifecycle
├── WearApp.kt                # Root composable + NavHost
├── AppContainer.kt           # Manual DI container
├── theme/
│   ├── Color.kt              # Material 3 color tokens
│   └── Theme.kt              # Wear Material 3 theme
├── data/
│   ├── ApiKeyStore.kt        # EncryptedSharedPreferences
│   ├── ChatMessage.kt        # Room entity
│   ├── ChatDao.kt            # Room DAO
│   ├── ChatDatabase.kt       # Room database
│   └── GeminiClient.kt       # Gemini API HTTP client
├── ui/
│   ├── onboarding/OnboardingScreen.kt
│   ├── chat/ChatScreen.kt    # Main chat interface
│   ├── chat/ChatViewModel.kt # Chat state management
│   └── settings/SettingsScreen.kt
└── tile/AssistantTileService.kt  # Wear Tile
```

## Key Design Decisions

- **AMOLED-first**: True black background (`#000000`) so inactive pixels stay off.
- **No background services**: 100% user-initiated. No polling, no WorkManager.
- **No wake locks**: Network calls cancel when the screen turns off.
- **Minimal animations**: Short (≤200ms) fade/slide, no looping/idle animations.
- **Encrypted API key**: Stored via `EncryptedSharedPreferences` (Android Keystore).
- **Local-only data**: Chat history stays in Room on-device — never synced.

## Available Gemini Models

| Setting | Model ID |
|---|---|
| Fast (default) | `gemini-2.5-flash-lite` |
| Balanced | `gemini-3.1-flash-lite` |
| Capable | `gemini-3.5-flash` |

Switch models in **Settings → Gemini Model**.
